Treasury Secretary Jacob J. Lew said
rising student-loan debt is hampering the U.S. economy and
additional steps need to be taken to make college more
affordable.  Lew made the remarks at a meeting today in  Washington  of
the Financial Literacy and Education Commission.  To contact the reporter on this story:
